node.text:
🛫 SKYDIVING LIVE VIDEO: You can reach everything in life, if you overcome your inner fears ... JUST DO IT !! What can we learn from skydiving? 🛬
⠀
✅ Those who don't jump will never fly.
⠀
✅  Do one thing every day that scares you.
⠀
✅ Skydiving changed my mindset. I am teaching my team and my kids, they could do anything and do it well, if they overcome fears.
⠀
✅ Once you have tasted flying or skydiving, you will never walk the earth with your eyes turned skyward, for there you have been, and there you will always long to return.
⠀
✅ I learned that courage was not the absence of fear, but the triumph over it. The brave man is not he who does not feel afraid, but he who conquers that fear.
⠀
✅ You don't need a parachute to skydive. You only need a parachute to skydive twice 😂🤣 ha ha ha 🤣😂.
⠀
. 
.

node.text:
🇺🇸❤️ In loving memory of THE VICTIMS. ❤️🇺🇸
🇺🇸❤️ In loving honor of THE HEROES. ❤️🇺🇸

👉🏼 If you see the picture on Page 2, this was taken in 2020, exactely 1 year before the terror attacks from 9/11. We visited the world trade center and did not even consider,  that 1 year later,  there is no WTC anymore. Then 9/11/2001  happened. We have been totally shocked, like most people. Thinking: what if this would have happened 1 year earlier? I realized,  you never know, how long you will be on planet earth, so enjoy every day, live in peace and harmony and be the best version of yourself....

👉🏼 I have so many friends and families in the USA, who where directly or indirectly effected from 9/11. Just thinking about this terrific scenario, brings tears 😢 into my eyes. The world has never been the same since then.

👉🏼 So much ❤ love for everyone, who lost someone through this. RIP.
I applaud 👏 to all the heros, who did not fear their lives on 9/11 and helped the victims and their families.

👉🏼 If we learn nothing else from this tragedy, we learn that life is short and there is no time for hate.

👉🏼 It was the worst day we have ever seen, but it brought out the best in all of us.” “One of the worst days in America's history saw some of the bravest acts in Americans' history. We'll always honor the heroes of 9/11. And here at this hallowed place, we pledge that we will never forget their sacrifice.
⠀

node.text:
🔑You did not wake up to be mediocre.🔑

✅ If you do NOT put your full focus, your best work, your best attitude, you total energy towards what you do, people will eventually become indifferent towards you, because what you do is ordinary and common. It's middle of the road. This applies to everything.

✅ We don’t want to think about our weaknesses. We don’t want to talk about them, and we certainly don’t want anyone else to point them out. This is a classic sign of mediocrity.

✅ Some people deny that they are mediocre, just because no one told them so. Excellence, is a better teacher than mediocrity. The lessons of the ordinary are everywhere. Truly profound and original insights are to be found only in studying the exemplary.

✅ You may often think of yourself: “Am I moderate? Do I give 100% of my potential? Am I good at my job?”. And you know what? The hunger of success is driven by your fear of mediocrity.

✅ Success can not be without mediocrity, “good” will not stand out if there was no “bad”.

✅ Accept yourself, do not be afraid to aim high, always listen to others but no take for granted their opinion. Just collect your “data”, analyze them inside your head and keep what YOU think is necessary. And do not be afraid or criticism. Only mediocrity escapes criticism.
⠀

🌊 Life is too short to think small. Chase your dreams. Make the impossible happen. 🌊
⠀
✅ You see things and you say 'Why?' But I dream things that never were; and I say 'Why not?
⠀
✅ You are never too old to set another goal or dream a new dream.
⠀
✅ Twenty years from now you will be more disappointed by the things you didn’t do than by the ones you did. So throw off the bowlines. Sail away from the safe harbor. Catch the trade winds in your sails. Explore. Dream. Discover.
⠀
✅ All successful people men and women are big dreamers. They imagine what their future could be, ideal in every respect, and then they work every day toward their distant vision, that goal or purpose.
⠀
✅ Never stretch your neck to see who is not doing it big. Look into your bosom, and realize that you can do it bigger! Go, create a brighter picture!
⠀
✅ People that live their lives with passion…never worry about competition.
⠀
✅ I always say, 'To have a big dream requires the same effort as having a small dream. So, better dream big! 
⠀

node.text:
🔑 Cut the bullshit from your life. Success is a mindset, because there are certain principles that exist, and if you follow these principles, you will become successful. 🔑
⠀
✅ One of these principles, is having firm boundaries, or in other words, not letting bullshit into your life. This means taking a stance when people or things try to mess with you.
⠀
✅ Bullshit comes in many forms—it can be that nagging girlfriend who won’t stop draining your energy, it can be that big mac you just ate, or it can even be your own thoughts. Sometimes, negative thought-loops are the worst kind of bullshit, because they’re in your own head!
⠀
✅ Whatever form it takes, however, one thing is for sure—the bullshit in your life will indefinitely prevent you from succeeding. This is why it is paramount that you cut it out, right now.
⠀
✅ Cut Out Bullshit Food. If you consume poor foods, you are literally creating a ripple effect that will fuck your life over and your brain and body won’t have the adequate nutrients to function. You’ll be slow to learn, have less energy, and will be less motivated.

In other words, your mind and body are being poisoned by bullshit food.
⠀
✅ Cut Out Bullshit Friends - As "you are the average of the 5 people you spend the most time with". (Jim Rohn)
⠀
✅ Cut Out Bullshit Habits! 
⠀
✅ Cut Out Bullshit Thoughts!
⠀

☀️ Good Summer Vibes 🔑Life is too short to think small. Chase your dreams. Make the impossible happen. 🔑
⠀
✅ You see things and you say 'Why?' But I dream things that never were; and I say 'Why not?
⠀
✅ You are never too old to set another goal or dream a new dream.
⠀
✅ Twenty years from now you will be more disappointed by the things you didn’t do than by the ones you did. So throw off the bowlines. Sail away from the safe harbor. Catch the trade winds in your sails. Explore. Dream. Discover.
⠀
✅ All successful people men and women are big dreamers. They imagine what their future could be, ideal in every respect, and then they work every day toward their distant vision, that goal or purpose.
⠀
✅ Never stretch your neck to see who is not doing it big. Look into your bosom, and realize that you can do it bigger! Go, create a brighter picture!
⠀
✅ People that live their lives with passion…never worry about competition.
⠀
✅ I always say, 'To have a big dream requires the same effort as having a small dream. So, better dream big! 
⠀

🔑 Successful people make decisions based on where they want to be.🔑
⠀
✅ Unsuccessful people make decisions based on their current situation.
⠀
✅ Successful people always look forward to goals they have set. Unsuccessful people focus on the circumstances around them. We can make excuses to why we are not achieving the success we desire or we can make the choice to move toward our goals despite the circumstances around us.
⠀
✅ Most people are simply unwilling to pay this price for success, and so remain in their average, mediocre lives.
⠀
✅ Most of the world doesn’t think they’re able to achieve greatness, so they don’t even try.
⠀
✅ Success is not achieved by chance, Success is achieved by consistency, discipline, and persistence.
⠀
✅ our level of success will rarely exceed your level of personal development, because success is something you attract by the person you become.
⠀
✅ But the ones who bite the bullet and commit are bound to achieve the success they want.
⠀
